Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Give examples of questions that require external documents to answer.  A good task requires information that is not found in the given document.
Input.Positive_Example_1: What other books were written by the novelist author?
Input.Positive_Example_2: Besides the theory discussed in this document, what other scientific theories explain the given phenomena?
Input.Positive_Example_3: Can you explain the term ÒmitochondriaÓ?
Input.Negative_Example_1: Questions that are unrelated to the documentÕs content
Answer.placeholder: Under what circumstances osmoprotection experiment can be applied?

Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Ask for a summary about parts of or the full document.  A good summarization task specifies the content to summarize and summary type (e.g., length, style)
Input.Positive_Example_1: Can you provide a concise summary of section 2?
Input.Positive_Example_2: Write a detailed summary about the main takeaways of the paper.
Input.Negative_Example_1: What is a summary of the document? (does not specify summary length)
Input.Negative_Example_2: Write a short summary. (does not specify summary content)
Answer.placeholder: List of Schools Having facilities ‐ Drinking Water, Boys Toilet and Girls Toilet

Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Ask for a summary about parts of or the full document.  A good summarization task specifies the content to summarize and summary type (e.g., length, style)

Input.Negative_Example_2: Write a short summary. (does not specify summary content)
Answer.placeholder: Can you provide a short summary of the full document?

Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Specify a figure in the document and ask a question about it.  A good question refers to a figure number or page in the document.
Input.Positive_Example_1: What is the main takeaway of Figure 4?
Input.Positive_Example_2: What is the largest value in Figure 4?
Input.Positive_Example_3: What kind of graph is used on page 5?
Input.Negative_Example_1: What is the main takeaway of the second graph? (missing reference to page or figure number)
Answer.placeholder: What other facilities required in school other than drinking water and toilet facilities?

Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Ask a question that references some structure in the document.
Input.Positive_Example_1: What is the main takeaway from section 5?
Input.Positive_Example_2: What counterexamples are provided in paragraph 3, section #1?
Input.Negative_Example_1: How many sections are there in the document? (too easy to answer)
Input.Negative_Example_2: What is the title of the document? (too easy to answer)

Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Ask a question about the contents of the document.  A good question can be fully answered by the information in the document and is not self-evident (not able to be verified with a quick scan).
Input.Positive_Example_2: What evidence is used to support the authorÕs conclusion in section #5?
Input.Negative_Example_1: What is the title of subsection #4? (too easy to answer)

Title: Brainstorm a Task for a Document
Description: Given a PDF and a type of task, brainstorm a new task for that document.
Input.Description: Write a question focusing on categorization of the document and/or its contents.
Input.Positive_Example_1: Is this document a scientific article?
Input.Positive_Example_2: Is this document about a residential lease or a commercial lease?
Input.Negative_Example_1: Categories that are unrelated to the document.
Answer.placeholder: Is this published during the years of Barrack Obama being the president?
